ProjectRevoTPP / FelkCraft Chat Log

"The Live Updates will stick with more frequent updates, with all important events bolded. With an equal split between those who want "less" and those who want "more", having updates bolded allows people to find the major events faster while others enjoy the smaller tidbits. It's probably not going to change, please don't ask." - /u/Inert_Berger

If you need a reference to the intermission updater, look no further!

[Info] So I heard that Ninjask evolved into Shedinja, and Shedinja evolved into Ninjask.

The way the bot determines if a given pokemon is the same pokemon before and after changes to it (like move learns, renames, evolutions, even swapping party order) is by comparing a hidden random number called the Personality Value, which never changes. This number is created when the pokemon is generated for an encounter, and is essentially unique to every pokemon... except when Nincada splits into a clone of itself when it evolves into both Ninjask and Shedinja simultaneously.

Basically, every update, the bot thought that Ninjask was evolving into Shedinja, and Shedinja was evolving into Ninjask, while also simultaneously thinking that Ninjask and Shedinja were not evolving. And you thought Shedinja's Wonder Guard was the only thing about Shedinja that broke things...
